Web Results  -    
Wings Around the World - http://www.worldwings.org/
Record-breaking solo flight in a single engine Piper Cherokee Dakota undertaken by Polly Vacher. Provides a picture gallery, diary, itinerary and route map.  

Tom Claytor Bush Pilot - http://www.claytor.com
Offering information on the travels of a bush pilot on a solo flight to seven continents.  

Dick Smith Flyer - http://www.dicksmithflyer.com.au/
Aviator Dick Smith comments on general aviation in Australia.  

David Williams Flying Homepage - http://www.dmjwilliams.co.uk/
Includes a photo gallery, aircraft flown, logbook, and links.  

Paul's Flying Diary - Ratings and Trip Reports - http://flying.guapacha.com
This site chronicles the flight training diary and 'interesting' flights that the author has taken.  

Flying In Ohio - http://flyingohio.blogspot.com/
A blog detailing the adventures of a private pilot in Ohio, also general aviation topics.  

Christer Lundholm - http://www.abc.se/~m9963/flyrken.html
Photography and information on the SAAB 340.  

Gene Seibel's Electric Flying Machine - http://pad39a.com/gene/plane.html
Offering information on a TriPacer. Stories, pictures, links.  

Raf Aerobatics - http://rafaero.free.fr/index-eng.html
Offers pictures, aerobatic history, animations, videos, and forum.  

Wings of the Wind - http://www.zone.com.br/parceiros/asasdovento/ingles/
Details a flight around the world by Gerard Moss in a Ximango. Information on aircraft, pilot, support team, log book and position.  

Carol Ann Garratt World Flight - http://www.kerrlake.com/mgarratt/index.htm
Pilot's editorial of trip around in the world in a Mooney.  

The Pilot Lounge Message Board - http://www.thepilotlounge.com
This site provides a location for pilots to discuss and share their aviation issues, experiences and adventures.  

Jim Foreman's Flying Stories - http://www.jimforeman.com/Stories/flying.htm
A collection of tales from a glider pilot and a builder of homemade aircraft.  

Holiday Flyer - http://www.holiday.flyer.co.uk/
The flying experiences of a British private pilot in Europe, Canada and US. Pictures and stories.  

Owen O'Malley and the RAAF 462 Squadron - http://www.ovomalley.com
Tribute to the late Owen O'Malley and members of the RAF/RAAF 462 Squadron. Includes rare photos.  

Fergworld - http://www.fergworld.com
Personal aviation experiences of a flight instructor. Includes training and reference section, articles, stories, and flying pictures.  

Eisenhard's Mooney - http://www.eisenhard.net/brucee/mooney/
Bruce and Nancy Eisenhard offers photos of a Mooney aircraft before and after restoration.  

NewFlight Student Pilot Experience Australia - http://www.newflight.net/
Offering student pilot experiences. Includes journals, pictures, reports, links, and aviation adventures.  

AV8 Ireland - http://www.iol.ie/~jordane/fly
Flying in Ireland, forum, photo gallery, space flight, and Salthill airshow, July 2001.  

Mary Creason's Aviation Website - http://members.aol.com/creasonwings
Offering info about pilot training, racing, scholarships, and aviation camp from a pilot with 60 years of aviation experience.  

Damir's Aviation Site - http://www.damir.co.uk/
Damir's flying experiences in the UK, with a list of airfields visited, air show pictures, and videos.  

Aeolus Aerospace - http://webs.lanset.com/aeolusaero/
A collection of aerospace life support equipment and the Christopher T. Carey opinions on American society.  

Bob Champine - http://hometown.aol.com/GRC6431/myhomepage/index.html
History of Bobs' aviation career; including some personal history and his involvement with both NACA, NASA, and model aviation.  

Honey Mooney's Home Page - http://www.honeymooney.com/
Pilot's world wide adventures in a Mooney aircraft. Includes logbook and photographs.  

Markus Rohrers Aviation Page - http://www.gear-up.ch
Offering information about an airline pilot's life. Includes bio and photo gallery.  

Nick's Aviation World - http://home.sprynet.com/~nhoffmann/
Offering insight by an Aircraft Dispatcher for a US Airline. Aircraft dispatch, aviation weather, flight simulator, aviation photography, aircraft spotting, and airline news.  

Tony Learns to Fly - http://www.tonylearnstofly.net

Kunal's Khatua's Homepage - http://members.tripod.com/SuperSabre/KKHomepage.htm

Sergei N.Stepanenko - http://www.geocities.com/CapeCanaveral/Hangar/7596

The Soares Aviation Web Site - http://home.earthlink.net/~soaresva/avpage.htm

Allan Hanbury's Homepage - http://allanhanbury.netfirms.com

Mike's Page - http://www.geocities.com/SouthBeach/Bay/3012

Lee Keller's Aerodrome - http://www.geocities.com/kswisslk01

Erez's Aviation Homepage - http://www.icfn.net/bluesky

Ben's Airshow Pages - http://www.geocities.com/bdt13/airshow.html

Mick Boyle's Aviation Page - http://www.ecn.net.au/%7emb/

Drew Mckee Mooney - http://hometown.aol.com/dmckee8283/

Hey Dad - http://groups.msn.com/HeyDad/

Patrick Smith Aviation Photos - http://www.kcle.8k.com

Flying for fun - http://flyto.mysite.wanadoo-members.co.uk/
John Crossland offers information on air trips.  

Frenchflyer's Home Page - http://www.frenchflyer.com/

Pfactor - Flying and Stuff - http://www.pfactor.com
